156
00:09:11,640 --> 00:09:13,360
In basketball, there's a technique

157
00:09:13,360 --> 00:09:15,200
called hang-time,

158
00:09:15,200 --> 00:09:17,040
which means a brief stay

159
00:09:17,040 --> 00:09:18,740
in the air after jumping

160
00:09:19,200 --> 00:09:20,740
before landing normally.

161
00:09:21,280 --> 00:09:23,240
Some top volleyball players

162
00:09:23,240 --> 00:09:24,160
can also achieve this.

163
00:09:24,160 --> 00:09:25,260
There are two benefits.

164
00:09:25,560 --> 00:09:28,520
First, it allows you
to avoid the block in the air.

165
00:09:28,520 --> 00:09:29,360
Second,

166
00:09:29,360 --> 00:09:30,680
it provides a more stable point

167
00:09:30,680 --> 00:09:32,340
for attacking in the air.

168
00:09:33,440 --> 00:09:34,360
I see.

169
00:09:34,360 --> 00:09:35,480
Similar to the fake moves

170
00:09:35,480 --> 00:09:37,180
Coach Tian taught me?

171
00:09:37,840 --> 00:09:38,920
That's true,

172
00:09:38,920 --> 00:09:40,840
but fake moves are common.

173
00:09:40,840 --> 00:09:42,620
Hang-time is more advanced.

174
00:09:44,800 --> 00:09:46,280
Do we have any special techniques?

175
00:09:46,280 --> 00:09:47,120
Yes.

176
00:09:47,280 --> 00:09:48,420
I've arranged it long ago.

177
00:09:50,880 --> 00:09:53,080
This is called the misalignment strategy.

178
00:09:53,080 --> 00:09:54,680
It's the most advanced technique

179
00:09:54,680 --> 00:09:55,860
in beach volleyball.

180
00:09:56,120 --> 00:09:58,080
It demands a lot from the setter

181
00:09:58,080 --> 00:09:58,920
and

182
00:09:59,040 --> 00:10:00,100
even more

183
00:10:00,360 --> 00:10:01,340
from the attackers.

184
00:10:03,760 --> 00:10:05,260
Both your dad and I think

185
00:10:05,520 --> 00:10:06,620
as long as one of you

186
00:10:06,840 --> 00:10:08,320
masters hang-time

187
00:10:08,320 --> 00:10:10,240
