222
00:11:49,600 --> 00:11:50,660
Let me say it again.

223
00:11:50,880 --> 00:11:52,200
Hang-time

224
00:11:52,200 --> 00:11:54,480
isn't just about staying

225
00:11:54,480 --> 00:11:55,400
in the air.

226
00:11:55,400 --> 00:11:56,980
It's about control.

227
00:11:57,320 --> 00:11:58,600
The longer you control in the air

228
00:11:58,600 --> 00:11:59,560
the center of gravity,

229
00:11:59,560 --> 00:12:00,800
the better your hang-time.

230
00:12:00,800 --> 00:12:01,640
Hang-time requires

231
00:12:01,640 --> 00:12:03,600
body coordination, balance,

232
00:12:03,600 --> 00:12:05,520
and core strength in your waist and abdomen.

233
00:12:05,520 --> 00:12:07,120
Do you remember what are the two steps

234
00:12:07,120 --> 00:12:08,740
on the powerful jump serve?

235
00:12:09,080 --> 00:12:12,180
Toss the ball, and then jump and spike.

236
00:12:12,640 --> 00:12:13,960
That's right. Now, it seems

237
00:12:13,960 --> 00:12:15,620
